’Ů@b3bef90b1cb46cbb69e699d5eab73f92fe1f8a22a6e3e8906d91d0e8366bf021ÚTitle: title: plugin rm
Path: Examples
Content:
Remove the installed signatures for the 
``inc``
 plugin.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> plugin rm inc


```
Remove the installed signatures for the plugin with the filename 
``~/.cargo/bin/nu_plugin_inc``
.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> plugin rm ~/.cargo/bin/nu_plugin_inc


```
Remove the installed signatures for the 
``polars``
 plugin from the "polars.msgpackz" plugin registry file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> plugin rm --plugin-config polars.msgpackz polars


```
’Ů@1953e26af210ca26876c5d7979f5a3904b0b6ea308aa820efacb46cf8ed9ce3aÚĘTitle: title: plugin rm
Path: Notes
Content:
This does not remove the plugin commands from the current scope or from 
``plugin list``
 in the current shell. It instead removes the plugin from the plugin

registry file (by default, 
``$nu.plugin-path``
). The changes will be apparent the

next time 
``nu``
 is launched with that plugin registry file.
This can be useful for removing an invalid plugin signature, if it can't be

fixed with 
``plugin add``
.
